{
  "stem": "18670.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They occupied the borders with Italy, with Czechoslovakia, with Yugoslavia, with Hungary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They occupied all the borders to Switzerland, to Luxembourg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The only border they didn't occupy was the border between Germany and Austria, because Austria became part of it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember being in Vienna when Hitler got into Vienna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was up at the Hotel Bristol on the balcony making a speech.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the women went hysterical.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They fell on the ground.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They kissed the ground and you would think it was Elvis Presley out there, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were-- and Hitler said-- I remember even the words he said, which were outstanding, that if not-- God is with him, because if not for God, he wouldn't be here in Austria.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "God is with him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And naturally, the weeks before the Nazis marched into Austria-- I don't know whether you're aware of it-- the Nazi party had been outlawed for years.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But in 1938, it became legal again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a fellow by the name of Schusschnigg who was the premier.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he invited them to come in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Actually, he and another fellow by the name of Seyss-Inquart, who had been put into the government.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "See , the story was in the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now that we have the National Socialist in the Austrian government, there's nothing to fear.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We have the horses before the wagon.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the horses ran away with the wagon.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You can't say increase, because it was always there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How could you miss it?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had Jewish refugees, German refugees come through, walking, hiking through Austria on the way to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother always had food waiting for them, not only them, every beggar.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
